    <note>Liu(2) Pu [13283] He was a granduncle of Anshi [13286] and gained fame as a literati (wenzhang) and for his classicism (ru). Anshi's grandfather, Zhi(3) [13264], was also an educated member of the gentry who was noted for solving litigation and for teaching his  sons and younger brothers. I am assuming that Pu is Zhi(3)'s cousin rather than brother and that Zhi(3) is the elder brother of Guan(3) [13290] (based on generational name), who was the great grandfather of Deli [13293] and his probable brother Deyan [13282]. Jiangxi TZ, 21.11b.</note>
